ck web developers to design and build systems, then use them to create & study novel human-AI interactions and answer open research questions in this space. Recent examples of work from our team include studying how to automate the work of data scientists (https://autoai.mybluemix.net/ ), for AI-assisted human-driven data labeling, and in collaborative partially-observable games between Human/AI partners (ibm.biz/learnplay). Required Technical and Professional Expertise Masters in Human-Computer Interaction, Human Factors, Computer Science, Information Science & Technology, Machine Learning, Artificial Intelligence, or related technical field Expertise and experience in programming in one or more of these languages: Python, Java, C, C++ Advanced skill level in solving analytical problems using rigorous and quantitative approaches Familiarity or experience with qualitative and quantitative research methodologies (such as interviewing, running A/B experiments, etc) and associated data analysis Experience communicating your research in technical communities, such as publications in CHI, IUI, CSCW, WWW, NIPS, CVPR, ICML, ICLR, IJCAI, AAAI, KDD, or similar Preferred Technical and Professional Expertise PhD in Human-Computer Interaction, Human Factors, Computer Science, Information Science & Technology, Machine Learning, Artificial Intelligence, or related technical fields Expertise and experience with full-stack web development, including HTML/CSS/Javascript, relational databases (such as Postgresql), and webserver frameworks (such as Flask, JavaEE, etc.) Experience creating and applying AI techniques specific to traditional machine learning and with standard machine learning techniques and frameworks including, but not limited to, Theano, Tensorflow, Caffe, Torch Experience with designing, building, and studying interactive systems User-centric design skills: such a wireframing, rapid prototyping, etc. About Business Unit With more than 3,000 researchers in 12 labs located across six continents, IBM Research brings together hundreds of researchers who possess unparalleled industry expertise to address some of the world's most challenging problems. Join us as we do pioneering work in areas such as cognitive computing, augmented intelligence, quantum computing, and blockchain, to name a few. Your Life @ IBM What matters to you when you\u2019re looking for your next career challenge? Maybe you want to get involved in work that really changes the world? What about somewhere with incredible and diverse career and development opportunities \u2013 where you can truly discover your passion? Are you looking for a culture of openness, collaboration and trust \u2013 where everyone has a voice? What about all of these? If so, then IBM could be your next career challenge. Join us, not to do something better, but to attempt things you never thought possible. Impact. Inclusion. Infinite Experiences. Do your best work ever. About IBM IBM\u2019s greatest invention is the IBMer. We believe that progress is made through progressive thinking, progressive leadership, progressive policy and progressive action. IBMers believe that the application of intelligence, reason and science can improve business, society and the human condition. Restlessly reinventing since 1911, we are the largest technology and consulting employer in the world, with more than 380,000 IBMers serving clients in 170 countries. Location Statement For additional information about location requirements, please discuss with the recruiter following submission of your application. Being You @ IBM IBM is committed to creating a diverse environment and is proud to be an equal opportunity employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, gender, gender identity or expression, sexual orientation, national origin, genetics, disability, age, or veteran status. IBM is also committed to compliance with all fair employment practices regarding citizenship and immigration status. ", 
